Lewis Hamilton snatched pole position for Sunday’s Azerbaijan Grand Prix after eclipsing Mercedes team-mate Valtteri Bottas on his final qualifying lap on Saturday. The three-time world champion starts ahead of Bottas with Ferrari duo Kimi Raikkonen and Sebastian Vettel occupying the second row of the grid. Hamilton claimed the 66th pole of his career, leaving the Briton just two shy of Michael Schumacher’s record of 68.